# Trivy Ignore File
# Path: .trivyignore
# Used to ignore specific vulnerabilities that are false positives or accepted risks

# Format: CVE-ID [reason] [expiry-date]
# Example: CVE-2023-12345 [Accepted risk: requires local access] 2024-12-31

# Node.js dependencies - accepted risks
# CVE-2022-XXXXX [Accepted: dev dependency only] 2024-12-31

# Python dependencies - false positives
# CVE-2023-XXXXX [False positive: not used in runtime] 2024-12-31

# OS packages in base images
# CVE-2024-XXXXX [Fixed in newer base image, will update] 2024-12-31

# Add your accepted risks below:
# Format: CVE-ID [reason] [expiry-date]

# Example entries (remove or modify as needed):
# CVE-2022-25883 [Accepted: only in dev dependencies, not in production image] 2024-12-31
# CVE-2023-48795 [SSH Terrapin: not applicable to our container] 2024-12-31